text.section:
The public education component of the program created in subsection (1) of this section shall include but not be limited to:
The cause and nature of osteoporosis;
Risk factors;
The role of oophorectomy and hysterectomy in the development of osteoporosis;
The prevention of osteoporosis, including nutrition, physical exercise, and weight;
Diagnostic procedures and appropriate indications for their use;
The risks and benefits of hormone replacement therapy;
Environment safety and injury prevention; and
Availability of osteoporosis treatment services in the community.
